<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Challenge 5: Cryptography</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <a href="/dashboard"><< Back to Hub</a>
        <h1>Challenge 5: Cryptographic Failures</h1>
        <div class="card">
            <p>Welcome to the VIP lounge. Only administrators are allowed to see the secret flag.</p>
            <p>It looks like the developer used a very weak encoding method for the 'role' cookie instead of proper encryption.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card">
            <h3>Access Panel</h3>
            <% if (error) { %>
                <div class="error"><%= error %></div>
            <% } else if (flag) { %>
                <div class="success">Welcome Admin! Here is your flag: <%= flag %></div>
            <% } %>
            
            <p>Your current role according to your cookie is: <strong><%= role %></strong></p>
            <p>Hint: Check your browser's Developer Tools (F12) -> Application/Storage -> Cookies.</p>
            <form action="/challenge/5" method="GET">
                <button type="submit">Refresh Page</button>
            </form>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
